<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-048-180  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 048 180.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Jan 13 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Computer Automation acquires needed funds.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Endrijonas, Janet.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Computer Automation Inc. (finance).andO;Ticker:    CAUT.andO;Topic:     Computer industryLoanFinancingStockStockholder.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMPUTER AUTOMATION ACQUIRES NEEDED FUNDS IRVINE, CALIFORNIA, U.S.A., 1990JAN 11 (NB) --  Computer Automation has entered into a loan, warrant andsecurity agreement with a group of private investors which has loaned thecompany $3,150,000 while the company has issued the investors warrants topurchase shares of its stock.andM;The loan is at 15 percent interest for a 24-month term.andP;  The loan is securedby all of the company's assets and guaranteed and/or secured by certainassets of the company's operating subsidiaries.andP;  The loan may be prepaid anytime.andM;The warrants granted to the lenders, including John F. Blokker, a director ofComputer Automation, entitle them to buy 315,000 shares of the company'scommon stock at $2 per share anytime after Jan. 5.andP;  Additional warrants havebeen granted to purchase 420,000 shares at $1 each after Apr. 30 if the loanhas not been repaid.andM;The money from this loan has been used to pay off Computer Automation'sprevious lender, Sanwa Bank California.andP;  Funds remaining after the payoff areearmarked to be used as working capital.andM;(Janet Endrijonas/19900112/Press Contact: William Osmundsen, ComputerAutomation, 714-833-8830)</TEXT></DOC>